Document: RefCounted
Path: godot/classes/class_refcounted.rst
Summary: Base class for reference-counted objects that are automatically freed when no longer in use.
Inherits: Object

RefCounted is the base class for any object that keeps a reference count. Resource and many other helper objects inherit this class.

Unlike other Object types, RefCounted instances keep an internal reference counter so that they are automatically released when no longer in use, and only then. RefCounted instances therefore do not need to be freed manually with Object.free().

RefCounted instances caught in a cyclic reference will not be freed automatically. For example, if a node holds a reference to instance A, which directly or indirectly holds a reference back to A, A's reference count will be 2. Destruction of the node will leave A dangling with a reference count of 1, and there will be a memory leak. To prevent this, one of the references in the cycle can be made weak with @GlobalScope.weakref().

In the vast majority of use cases, instantiating and using RefCounted-derived types is all you need to do. The methods provided in this class are only for advanced users, and can cause issues if misused.

Note: In C#, reference-counted objects will not be freed instantly after they are no longer in use. Instead, garbage collection will run periodically and will free reference-counted objects that are no longer in use. This means that unused ones will remain in memory for a while before being removed.
---CHUNK---
Document: RefCounted
Path: godot/classes/class_refcounted.rst
Summary: Provides a basic reference counting mechanism for objects.

RefCounted is a base class that provides a basic reference counting mechanism. This is useful for objects that are shared between multiple parts of your game and need to be deallocated automatically when no longer in use.

When you inherit from RefCounted, you get two methods: `reference()` and `unreference()`.

- `reference()`: Increments the reference count.
- `unreference()`: Decrements the reference count.

When the reference count reaches zero, the object is automatically freed.

Key Rule: RefCounted objects are reference-counted. You must manually call `reference()` when you want to keep a reference to the object and `unreference()` when you are done with it. If you forget to call `unreference()`, the object will never be freed, leading to a memory leak.

Example:

GDScript:
```gdscript
extends RefCounted

var data = "some data"

func _init():
    print("RefCounted object created")

func _destroy():
    print("RefCounted object destroyed")

var my_ref = MyRefCounted.new()
print("Initial reference count: ", my_ref.get_reference_count()) # Output: 1

var another_ref = my_ref
another_ref.reference() # Increment reference count
print("Reference count after another_ref: ", my_ref.get_reference_count()) # Output: 2

another_ref.unreference() # Decrement reference count
print("Reference count after unreference: ", my_ref.get_reference_count()) # Output: 1

my_ref.unreference() # Decrement reference count
print("Reference count after final unreference: ", my_ref.get_reference_count()) # Output: 0 (object will be freed)
```

C#:
```csharp
using Godot;
using System;

public class MyRefCounted : RefCounted
{
    public MyRefCounted()
    {
        GD.Print("RefCounted object created");
    }

    public override void _Destroy()
    {
        GD.Print("RefCounted object destroyed");
    }
}

public class Example : Node
{
    public override void _Ready()
    {
        MyRefCounted myRef = new MyRefCounted();
        GD.Print($"Initial reference count: {myRef.GetReferenceCount()}"); // Output: 1

        MyRefCounted anotherRef = myRef;
        anotherRef.Reference(); // Increment reference count
        GD.Print($"Reference count after anotherRef: {myRef.GetReferenceCount()}"); // Output: 2

        anotherRef.Unreference(); // Decrement reference count
        GD.Print($"Reference count after Unreference: {myRef.GetReferenceCount()}"); // Output: 1

        myRef.Unreference(); // Decrement reference count
        GD.Print($"Reference count after final Unreference: {myRef.GetReferenceCount()}"); // Output: 0 (object will be freed)
    }
}
```
